summary: What this blog means to me.
title: What this blog means to me.
body:
So I’m a small Tumblr blog. I’m not as big as @pukicho or @staff. Or even in this small Andi Mack community, @disneymack (fun fact: Ive been hear longer than them) But I’m still fairly sizeable. I barely post on the weeks and I am barely even an Andi Mack Tumblr user, especially as they show is ending. But I would like you all to know how much you mean to me. 


There I told you what you mean to me. 




JK. (wow. Am I a fucking 40 year old women on Facebook? I think the fuck not) But even though my older posts we’re more popular, and nobody ever tells me what they want from me, I do this for you guys. 

Like,  The Jyrus Shipper that wants a blog that is not about Tyrus and cares about meditating the ship wars rather than adding fuel to the fire.

Or, The Older Teen Viewers that are made fun of, for being Teens (like 14-17) and watch this show.

Or, the LGBTQ+ veiwers, that know that they’re no different just like Cyrus.

Or just anyone that watches Andi Mack, because we’re all special, and even if we disagree or enjoy different things we are still United by this one thing that feels like we’ve been family forever, but in reality for only 2 years (and I’ve only been here since last February) And we’re breaking up soon. But we’ll always have our reunions, and it’ll feel like old times again, but I ain’t no motherfuckin sentimental person, so let’s not get ahead of ourselves.

Or if you do something else I enjoy like The Sims or Just Dance or One Day At A Time or The Good Place or Superstore, and anything else I might’ve talked about.

And while this sounds like a good bye it is actually a hello. Hello, to all my old friends and hello to all my new ones and the friends I haven’t met yet. Hello to the people that liked my shitpost. Hello to the people that used art I created a long time ago. Hello to you. You are the ones that got me to 250 followers (boy what’s gonna happen when I hit 500 or even 1000?) And I’d like to say thank you. But I’ll also say your welcome. 


Hello to a new beginning.

summary: Lamb’s Lament
title: Lamb’s Lament
body:
Disappointment.

A word that means so much, and carries so much weight. A feeling that Cyrus figured he should be used to by now. For things never really went his way. Really, he should know better by now he thought. 

Cyrus thought that things would be different this time. TJ had always believed in him- or he atleast pretended to. Cyrus also had reason to believe that TJ was become a kinder person and cared about him. Even if TJ was nicer than he was before they became friends though, that doesn’t mean he cares about Cyrus any more than just a regular friend if it all.

Cyrus should have seen the Kira thing coming. TJ had been hanging out with her, and while TJ and Buffy may have cleared the air enough to become friends, they most likely would never be extra close. Him and Kira though- why not? They both love basketball- and there’s no denying that she’s pretty.

It’s not even the costume change that bothers him the most. Basketball was TJ’s thing before “somersault” became there’s. Does he he hate that he was chosen over, of course, but he’ll get over that. It’s not the first time he’s been the last choice. As glad as he is too have a friend like Jonah, Cyrus is used to being in his shadow. What affects him the most, is that TJ didn’t even try to contact him before school. TJ just let him show up in his part of the costume, muttered a quick “sorry” and left.

Just to show how much he means to TJ, if TJ didn’t even think about explaining it. Cyrus had ditched his friends for this. Cyrus was wrong about TJ apparently. Cyrus didn’t matter to TJ, and quite frankly, he was tired of being hurt by TJ wether accidently or not.

Cyrus wasn’t mad though. He was just severely disappointed in TJ and in himself for getting his hopes up.

Cyrus doesn’t know if he could forgive TJ like this. For some reason- this time he was hit deeper than he was with the gun situation. Cyrus knew he should talk to TJ though. Cyrus isn’t the type of person to not let someone explain themselves later on. Maybe Cyrus just wants there to be a deeper reason for why TJ would do this that would make everything make sense, but either way, Cyrus couldn’t just end things now. He didn’t have the heart. 

Right now though, Cyrus couldn’t bear to face TJ. The talk will have to wait, and for now, his thoughts will remain a lamb’s lament.

summary:
Ok, unpopular opinion or something, but i really don’t like when people say, that Tj changed for Cyrus. 
Cause you should never...
body:
Ok, unpopular opinion or something, but i really don’t like when people say, that Tj changed for Cyrus.

Cause you should never change for another person for good or for bad, because then when the person is gone, the change, well… goes away with them

And i seriously don’t think tj did that. I think he did that for himself. I think Cyrus just helped him with it. Tj saw in Cyrus that kindness exists. And he saw kindness in himself. We also see it after the gun thing. Tj doesn’t have a promise that after doing ,the right thing’ Cyrus will be back. Even, it seems like Cy doesn’t want to talk to him and won’t start suddenly. But he does what he thinks was right. He changed and we can see it.

Cyrus showed tj the possibility, but it is tj who changed, it was his deccision to be a better person. Tj Kippen changed for himself

And maybe on the way he fell in love
